an Signal Processing Conference (EUSIPCO) ,\n1301\t \n1302\t Vol. , pp. 897–901 .\n1303\t \n1304\t External Links: Document \n1305\t \n1306\t Cited by: §4.3 ,\n1307\t §4.3 ,\n1308\t Table 3 ,\n1309\t footnote 2 .\n1310\t \n1311\t \n1312\t\n1313\t- \n1314\t [10] \n1315\t Y. Fu, L. Cheng, S. Lv, et al. (2021) \n1316\t \n1317\t AISHELL-4: an open source dataset for speech enhancement, separation, recognition and speaker diarization in conference scenario .\n1318\t \n1319\t In Proc. ISCA Interspeech ,\n1320\t \n1321\t pp. 3665–3669 .\n1322\t \n1323\t Cited by: §3 .\n1324\t \n1325\t \n1326\t\n1327\t- \n1328\t [11] \n1329\t A. Gulati, J. Qin, C. Chiu, N. Parmar, Y. Zhang, J. Yu, W. Han, S. Wang, Z. Zhang, Y. Wu, and R. Pang (2020) \n1330\t \n1331\t Conformer: convolution-augmented transformer for speech recognition .\n1332\t \n1333\t In Proc. ISCA Interspeech ,\n1334\t \n1335\t pp. 5036–5040 .\n1336\t \n1337\t External Links: Document ,\n1338\t ISSN 2958-1796 \n1339\t \n1340\t Cited by: §1 .\n1341\t \n1342\t \n1343\t\n1344\t- \n1345\t [12] \n1346\t J. Han, F. Landini, J. Rohdin, A. Silnova, M. Diez, and L. Burget (2025) \n1347\t \n1348\t Leveraging self-supervised learning for speaker diarization .\n1349\t \n1350\t In Proc. IEEE ICASSP ,\n1351\t \n1352\t Cited by: §1 ,\n1353\t §1 ,\n1354\t §3 ,\n1355\t Table 1 .\n1356\t \n1357\t \n1358\t\n1359\t- \n1360\t [13] \n1361\t J. Han, P. Pálka, M. Delcroix, F. Landini, J. Rohdin, J. Černocký, and L. Burget (2026) \n1362\t \n1363\t Efficient and robust speaker diarization via structured pruning of self-supervised models .\n1364\t \n1365\t IEEE Trans. Audio, Speech, Lang. Process. 34 ( ), pp. 1903–1914 .\n1366\t \n1367\t Cited by: §3 ,\n1368\t §4.3 ,\n1369\t Table 3 .\n1370\t \n1371\t \n1372\t\n1373\t- \n1374\t [14] \n1375\t J. Han, R. Wang, Y. Masuyama, M. Delcroix, J. Rohdin, J. Du, and L. Burget (2025) \n1376\t \n1377\t Spatially aware self-supervised models for multi-channel neural speaker diarization .\n1378\t \n1379\t In arXi