{"type": "assistant", "message": {"id": "msg_1784124339162", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "我现在已经建立了关键的事实锚点。让我获取参考文献 [8] (arXiv:2601.02231) 的摘要，以理解其与当前论文的关系，因为这篇论文在本质上依赖于它。"}], "model": "GLM-5.2-w4a8", "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 0, "output_tokens": 0, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "6379eb56-72ac-4393-84e1-e3a485be1b01", "uuid": "4a814b78-d5d8-49ca-972b-e4660d56ba9e"}
{"type": "assistant", "message": {"id": "msg_1784124339162", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "chatcmpl-tool-8e86d438b7ed7f1b", "name": "Bash", "input": {"command": "curl -sL \"https://arxiv.org/abs/2601.02231\" 2>&1 | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, re\nhtml = sys.stdin.read()\n# Extract abstract\nm = re.search(r'<blockquote class=\\\"abstract[^>]*>.*?</blockquote>', html, re.DOTALL)\nif m:\n    text = re.sub(r'<[^>]+>', '', m.group())\n    text = re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', text).strip()\n    print('ABSTRACT:', text)\n# Extract title\nm = re.search(r'<h1 class=\\\"title[^>]*>.*?</h1>', html, re.DOTALL)\nif m:\n    text = re.sub(r'<[^>]+>', '', m.group()).strip()\n    print('TITLE:', text)\n\" 2>&1 | head -30", "description": "Fetch abstract of ref [8] from arxiv"}}], "model": "GLM-5.2-w4a8", "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 0, "output_tokens": 0, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "6379eb56-72ac-4393-84e1-e3a485be1b01", "uuid": "e8bea09a-a0a9-4085-9d7f-16c45fac5977"}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-8e86d438b7ed7f1b", "type": "tool_result", "content": "ABSTRACT: Abstract:Recent advances in speaker diarization exploit large pretrained foundation models, such as WavLM, to achieve state-of-the-art performance on multiple datasets. Systems like DiariZen leverage these rich single-channel representations, but are limited to single-channel audio, preventing the use of spatial cues available in multi-channel recordings. This work analyzes the impact of incorporating spatial information into a state-of-the-art single-channel diarization system by evaluating several strategies for conditioning the model on multi-channel spatial features. Experiments on meeting-style datasets indicate that spatial information can improve diarization performance, but the overall improvement is smaller than expected for the proposed system, suggesting that the features aggregated over all WavLM layers already capture much of the information needed for accurate speaker discrimination, also in overlapping speech regions. These findings provide insight into the potential and limitations of using spatial cues to enhance foundation model-based diarization.\nTITLE: Title:On the Role of Spatial Features in Foundation-Model-Based Speaker Diarization", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "6379eb56-72ac-4393-84e1-e3a485be1b01", "uuid": "c5506167-487d-4a68-9284-4efb105a3923", "timestamp": "2026-07-15T14:06:00.736Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "ABSTRACT: Abstract:Recent advances in speaker diarization exploit large pretrained foundation models, such as WavLM, to achieve state-of-the-art performance on multiple datasets. Systems like DiariZen leverage these rich single-channel representations, but are limited to single-channel audio, preventing the use of spatial cues available in multi-channel recordings. This work analyzes the impact of incorporating spatial information into a state-of-the-art single-channel diarization system by evaluating several strategies for conditioning the model on multi-channel spatial features. Experiments on meeting-style datasets indicate that spatial information can improve diarization performance, but the overall improvement is smaller than expected for the proposed system, suggesting that the features aggregated over all WavLM layers already capture much of the information needed for accurate speaker discrimination, also in overlapping speech regions. These findings provide insight into the potential and limitations of using spatial cues to enhance foundation model-based diarization.\nTITLE: Title:On the Role of Spatial Features in Foundation-Model-Based Speaker Diarization", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
{"type": "assistant", "message": {"id": "msg_1784124374844", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "这是一个关键发现。参考文献 [8] (arXiv:2601.02231) 由相同的第一作者 (Marc Deegen) 和部分相同的作者团队（包括 Reinhold Haeb-Umbach）撰写，提出了条件化方法，这是当前论文中表现最好的系统。当前论文将其构建为一项“比较研究”，但表现最好的方法直接采用了他们之前的工作。让我再进行最后一次搜索来确认时间关系。"}], "model": "GLM-5.2-w4a8", "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 0, "output_tokens": 0, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "6379eb56-72ac-4393-84e1-e3a485be1b01", "uuid": "6c1f83eb-264c-4c73-97c7-80883429f6df"}
